1:1 COMMENT "# generator_map_filter.z -- a two-stage generator pipeline."
1:60 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `intrange` produces a finite stream of integers; `doubled`"
3:61 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# transforms each one (the map stage); `greater_than` keeps only"
4:65 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# the values above a threshold (the filter stage); `main` drives"
5:65 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# the composed pipeline."
6:25 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#"
7:2 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# Each stage is a generator that takes parameters and constructs"
8:65 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# the next stage inline as the for-loop's iterable. The P9"
9:59 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# inline-iterable promotion (`_promote_suspending_for_iterables`"
10:65 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# in src/zgenerator.py) auto-extracts each non-trivial for-loop"
11:64 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# RHS into a synthetic local, so the sub-iterator persists as a"
12:64 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# field of the outer iterator's synthesised class. Existing"
13:60 EOL "\n"
14:1 COMMENT "# lock-escape rules apply through the captured-field machinery."
14:64 EOL "\n"
15:1 COMMENT "#"
15:2 EOL "\n"
16:1 COMMENT "# Pipeline shape:"
16:18 EOL "\n"
17:1 COMMENT "#   intrange  --(yields)-->  doubled  --(yields)-->  greater_than"
17:66 EOL "\n"
18:1 COMMENT "#"
18:2 EOL "\n"
19:1 COMMENT "# For `lo: 1, hi: 6` the inner intrange yields 1..5; doubled"
19:61 EOL "\n"
20:1 COMMENT "# emits 2/4/6/8/10; greater_than(threshold: 5) keeps 6/8/10."
20:61 EOL "\n"
21:1 COMMENT "# See doc/spec.pdoc Generator functions / Composability."
21:57 EOL "\n"
22:1 EOL "\n"
